  "data": [
    {
      "type": "p",
      "property": null,
      "children": "There are various techniques you can employ to snap a screenshot on a Windows 10 or Windows 11 PC."
    },
    {
      "type": "br",
      "property": null,
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "property": null,
      "children": "We've picked together the best ways to snap a Windows screenshot, whether you want to save the entire screen or just a portion of it."
    },
    {
      "type": "br",
      "property": null,
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "property": null,
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "strong",
          "property": null,
          "children": "1. The Print Screen button"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "img",
      "property": {
        "src": "https://karanmanral.github.io/site_data/blog/how-to-take-screenshot-on-windows/images/prtsc1.webp",
        "className": "blogImg",
        "loading": "lazy",
        "alt": "PrtScn",
        "title": "PrtScn"
      },
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "property": null,
      "children": "By hitting the Print Screen (PrtScn) key on your keyboard, you may quickly snap a screenshot of your full screen in Windows 10 or Windows 11."
    },
    {
      "type": "img",
      "property": {
        "src": "https://karanmanral.github.io/site_data/blog/how-to-take-screenshot-on-windows/images/prtsc2.webp",
        "className": "blogImg",
        "loading": "lazy",
        "alt": "MS Paint",
        "title": "MS Paint"
      },
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "property": null,
      "children": "The screenshot will be transferred to your clipboard. Use any program, such as Microsoft Word or Paint, that lets you input photos to save the file by pasting the screenshot into it."
    },
    {
      "type": "br",
      "property": null,
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "property": null,
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "strong",
          "property": null,
          "children": "2. The Windows key + Print Screen"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "img",
      "property": {
        "src": "https://karanmanral.github.io/site_data/blog/how-to-take-screenshot-on-windows/images/wdprtsc.webp",
        "className": "blogImg",
        "loading": "lazy",
        "alt": "Windows + PrtScn",
        "title": "Windows + PrtScn"
      },
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "property": null,
      "children": "Press the Windows key + PrtScn to take a screenshot in Windows 10 or Windows 11 and have the file saved automatically to the Screenshots folder."
    },
    {
      "type": "br",
      "property": null,
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "property": null,
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "strong",
          "property": null,
          "children": "3. The Snip & Sketch tool in Windows"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "img",
      "property": {
        "src": "https://karanmanral.github.io/site_data/blog/how-to-take-screenshot-on-windows/images/snip1.webp",
        "className": "blogImg",
        "loading": "lazy",
        "alt": "The Snip & Sketch tool",
        "title": "The Snip & Sketch tool"
      },
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "property": null,
      "children": "If you want to personalise, annotate, or share your screenshots, the Windows 10 Snip & Sketch app is the finest method to snapshot on Windows. As it provides editing tools like an eraser, a ruler, and cropping tools, this is the easiest approach to annotate your screenshots before sharing them."
    },
    {
      "type": "br",
      "property": null,
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "property": null,
      "children": "Use Windows Key + Shift + S on the keyboard to launch Snip & Sketch. You'll have the choice to take a rectangular, free-form, window, or full-screen capture once your screen dims and a little menu pops up at the top of it."
    },
    {
      "type": "img",
      "property": {
        "src": "https://karanmanral.github.io/site_data/blog/how-to-take-screenshot-on-windows/images/snip2.webp",
        "className": "blogImg",
        "loading": "lazy",
        "alt": "The Snip & Sketch tool in Windows",
        "title": "The Snip & Sketch tool in Windows"
      },
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "property": null,
      "children": "After you take the screenshot, it will be saved to your clipboard and a preview notification will show in the bottom-right corner of your screen."
    },
    {
      "type": "br",
      "property": null,
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "property": null,
      "children": "To save, share, or alter the snapshot using the various drawing tools, click the preview notice to launch the Snip & Sketch app."
    },
    {
      "type": "br",
      "property": null,
      "children": null
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "property": null,
